{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d41e4d4f-7cf4-4437-b90b-90c1a07f424d","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .dmp crash dump! Here's what you can do:\n\n**On this Linux environment**, install and use `dotnet-dump`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <your-file>.dmp\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `pe` | Print last exception (start here!) |\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `threads` | List all threads |\n| `clrstack -all` | Stacks for all threads |\n| `dso` | Dump stack objects |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary |\n\n**Typical workflow:**\n1. `pe` → see the exception type & message\n2. `clrstack` → see where it crashed\n3. `threads` → check for deadlocks or other faulting threads\n\n**Alternatively**, on Windows you can use:\n- **Visual Studio** → File > Open > File > select the `.dmp`\n- **WinDbg** with SOS: `!analyze -v`, `!pe`, `!clrstack`\n\n---\n\nWould you like to upload the `.dmp` file to this environment so I can run `dotnet-dump analyze` on it, or do you need help with a specific step?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8c77b892-0904-4e57-8d3a-c4180dc12e0b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET app and wants to analyze it. Let me think about what tools and approaches are available.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I don't see a specific skill for analyzing .dmp crash dump files. The skills available are:\n- `dump-collect` - but this is for **collecting** dumps, NOT analyzing them\n- `dotnet-trace-collect` - for collecting traces, not analyzing dumps\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - for Android tombstone files\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - for Apple .ips crash logs\n\nNone of these skills are for analyzing a .dmp file. \n\nSince I don't have a dedicated skill for dump analysis, I'll need to guide the user through manual approaches using standard debugging tools like WinDbg or dotnet-dump commands that should be available in their environment.","outputTokens":545,"requestId":"2042:3131A1:64DEE61:6DC3462:69F01359"},"id":"a9072a6a-61f2-4810-9eae-ba24de4e7c6e","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:54:47.069Z","parentId":"5d056eac-74ac-4c44-afb1-ae6f626d6629"}
